${PAR}SOLUTION:${PAR}

a. Find the partial derivatives of the original function.
$BR
\(f_x(x,y)=$revx\) 
$BR
\(f_y(x,y)=$revy\) 
$BR
\(f_{xx}(x,y)=$revxx\) 
$BR
\(f_{xy}(x,y)=$revxy\) 
$BR
\(f_{yy}(x,y)=$revyy\) 
$BR
$BR
b. Find the critical point in the region.
$BR
The point is  \($critpnt\).
$BR
$BR
c. Compute the discriminant at the critical point.
$BR
The discriminant is  \($revxx*$revyy-$revxy^2=$disc\)
$BR
d. Determine if the critical point is a maxima, minima, or saddle point.
$BR
If the discriminant and \(f_x(x,y)\) are both positive at the critical point, it is a minimum.
$BR
If the discriminant is positive and \(f_x(x,y)\) is negative at the critical point, it is a maximum.
$BR
If the discriminant is negative at the critical point, it is a saddle point.
$BR


